Lagos State has recorded one additional COVID-19 related death, bringing the total deaths so far to 31. The Lagos State Ministry of Health disclosed this on its verified Twitter handle @LSMOH. According to the update, as at May 4, 2020, 76 new cases of COVID-19 infection was confirmed, raising the total confirmed cases in Lagos 1,199. Also, 14 patients including eight males and six females were discharged on May 4, bringing to 261, the total number of cases successfully managed and discharged in the State. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Lagos records 2 more COVID-19 deaths, total now 30 COVID-19 death toll rises to 28 in Lagos Lagos announces death of 36-year-old COVID-19 patient